---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { breadcrumbSchema } from "../../data/schemas";

const lang = "en";

const jsonLd = breadcrumbSchema([
  { name: "Home", url: "/en" },
  { name: "Privacy Policy" },
]);
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | SNA Acoustic Consultancy"
  description="Privacy policy of SNA Acoustic Consultancy. Information on personal data processing, GDPR rights, and cookie usage."
  canonical="https://snaconsultoriaacustica.com/en/privacy-policy/"
  lang="en"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 lg:pt-40 lg:pb-28">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-justify leading-relaxed">
      <h1 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold mb-10">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mb-8">Following the principles of legality, fairness, and transparency, we make this Privacy Policy available to you.</p>

      <!-- Data controller -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Who is responsible for processing your data?</h2>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-muted/60 p-5 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-1">
          <p><strong>Legal name:</strong> SNA Consultoría Acústica</p>
          <p><strong>CIF:</strong> B-24661738</p>
          <p><strong>Registered address:</strong> Torre Europa, Paseo de la Castellana, 95, planta 29, 28046 Madrid</p>
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> info@snaconsultoriaacustica.com</p>
          <p><strong>Phone:</strong> 91 838 78 66</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Purpose -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">What is the purpose of processing your personal data?</h2>
        <p>At SNA Acoustic Consultancy we process the information you provide to manage the contractual relationship between us.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Retention -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">How long will we keep your personal data?</h2>
        <p>Your data will be retained for the minimum time necessary for the correct provision of the service offered and to meet any responsibilities that may arise from it and any other legal requirement.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Legal basis -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">What is the legal basis for processing your data?</h2>
        <p>The legal basis for the processing of your personal data is the consent of the data subject. The data we request is adequate, relevant, and strictly necessary, and you are in no case obliged to provide it, but failure to do so may affect the purpose of the service or make it impossible to provide.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Recipients -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">To which recipients will your data be communicated?</h2>
        <p>SNA Acoustic Consultancy will not communicate your data to any third party, unless expressly informed otherwise.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Rights -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">What are your rights when you provide us with your data?</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">The data protection rights held by data subjects are:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>Right to request access to personal data relating to the data subject</li>
          <li>Right to rectification or erasure</li>
          <li>Right to object</li>
          <li>Right to request restriction of processing</li>
          <li>Right to data portability</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Data subjects may exercise their personal data protection rights by sending a written communication to the registered address of SNA Acoustic Consultancy or to the email address info@snaconsultoriaacustica.com, including in both cases a copy of their ID or equivalent identification document.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Consent -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Can I withdraw consent?</h2>
        <p>You have the possibility and right to withdraw consent for any specific purpose granted at the time, without affecting the lawfulness of the processing based on consent prior to its withdrawal.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Complaints -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Where can I file a complaint if I believe my data is not being processed correctly?</h2>
        <p>If any data subject considers that their data is not being processed correctly by SNA Acoustic Consultancy, they can send their complaints to info@snaconsultoriaacustica.com or to the relevant data protection authority, which in Spain is the AEPD.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Security -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Security and update of your personal data</h2>
        <p>In order to safeguard the security of your personal data, we inform you that SNA Acoustic Consultancy has adopted all necessary technical and organisational measures to guarantee the security of the personal data provided.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Confidentiality -->
      <div class="border-b border-sna-gray-line pb-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>SNA Acoustic Consultancy informs you that your data will be treated with the utmost care and confidentiality by all personnel involved in any phase of the processing. We will not transfer or communicate your data to any third party, except in legally provided cases, or unless the data subject has expressly authorised us.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Cookies -->
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-sna-gray-line bg-muted/30 p-6 lg:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-primary/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-primary">Cookies</span>
          <h2 class="border-l-2 border-primary pl-3 text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Cookie information</h2>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">What is a Cookie?</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">A cookie is a small text file that a website places on your PC, phone, or any other device, with information about your browsing on that site.</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">What are cookies used for on this website?</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">Cookies are an essential part of how our website works. The main purpose of our cookies is to improve your browsing experience.</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">What are cookies NOT used for on this website?</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">We do not store sensitive personal identification information such as your address, password, credit or debit card details, etc., in the cookies we use.</p>
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Can cookies be deleted?</h3>
        <p>Yes, and not only deleted but also blocked, either generally or specifically for a particular domain.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
